1
00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:06,031
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:08,155 --> 00:00:10,655
(Lee Na Young)

3
00:00:16,525 --> 00:00:19,425
(Jung Eun Chae)

4
00:00:20,995 --> 00:00:23,705
(Lee Chung Ah)

5
00:00:31,075 --> 00:00:35,075
(Honour)

6
00:00:35,615 --> 00:00:38,455
(Supported by the Culture Ministry
and Korea's Creative Content Agency)

7
00:00:38,915 --> 00:00:40,121
(All people, incidents, and backgrounds...)

8
00:00:40,145 --> 00:00:41,661
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

9
00:00:41,685 --> 00:00:44,445
(Also, children and animals were
filmed under production guidelines.)

10
00:01:23,765 --> 00:01:24,965
Are you coming to your senses?

11
00:01:29,535 --> 00:01:30,935
You remember this place, don't you?

12
00:01:31,965 --> 00:01:33,405
This used to be your favourite spot.

13
00:01:34,075 --> 00:01:35,851
Because no one would come
even if you beat someone.

14
00:01:35,875 --> 00:01:37,155
Min Seo, what's gotten into you?

15
00:01:38,175 --> 00:01:39,245
What are you doing?

16
00:01:39,545 --> 00:01:40,545
You know, right?

17
00:01:41,115 --> 00:01:42,435
And no one's coming today either.

18
00:01:43,545 --> 00:01:44,545
Min Seo.

19
00:01:47,685 --> 00:01:48,685
Min Seo.

20
00:01:49,255 --> 00:01:50,255
Please.

21
00:01:51,425 --> 00:01:54,195
You're not like this.
You're a good kid, right?

22
00:01:54,625 --> 00:01:56,265
How could you do this to your own mother?

23
00:01:56,855 --> 00:01:58,195
Min Seo, please.

24
00:01:58,765 --> 00:02:00,025
Please.

25
00:02:00,695 --> 00:02:01,695
Please.

26
00:02:02,735 --> 00:02:04,065
Please, Min Seo.

27
00:02:34,665 --> 00:02:35,665
Sweet dreams,

28
00:02:36,665 --> 00:02:37,665
Mom.

29
00:02:59,185 --> 00:03:00,925
(Episode 7)

30
00:03:06,795 --> 00:03:08,995
Min Seo, I'm here.

31
00:03:18,245 --> 00:03:20,375
- Min Seo?
- Yes, Attorney.

32
00:03:23,615 --> 00:03:26,095
Can you come out for a second?
I have a few questions for you.

33
00:03:35,925 --> 00:03:38,265
- Min Seo.
- I'll be right out.

34
00:04:01,415 --> 00:04:03,355
What? Lee Seon Hwa's missing?

35
00:04:03,515 --> 00:04:05,501
I waited a long time for
her at our meeting place,

36
00:04:05,525 --> 00:04:08,225
- but now I can't get ahold of her.
- Find her. Whatever it takes.

37
00:04:08,925 --> 00:04:09,925
Now!

38
00:04:34,155 --> 00:04:35,215
I know you're awake.

39
00:05:14,925 --> 00:05:16,831
The number you have dialled
is not available. After the beep...

40
00:05:16,855 --> 00:05:18,335
She's not picking up my calls either.

41
00:05:18,725 --> 00:05:22,695
Is there anyone else we
can call? Family, friends?

42
00:05:27,005 --> 00:05:28,325
As for a place she might've gone,

43
00:05:29,475 --> 00:05:31,275
there is one place that comes to mind.

44
00:05:36,315 --> 00:05:38,545
So this is the place you meant, Min Seo?

45
00:05:39,345 --> 00:05:41,985
- We came here often as a kid.
- I see, but

46
00:05:42,685 --> 00:05:44,725
I doubt she'd come here now.

47
00:05:45,255 --> 00:05:48,225
She wouldn't have any money,
and she'd need to stay hidden.

48
00:05:50,095 --> 00:05:52,765
This is the safest place
that Lee Seon Hwa knows.

49
00:06:00,105 --> 00:06:01,205
Aren't you going in?

50
00:06:44,845 --> 00:06:46,445
Looks like kids still come here.

51
00:07:05,905 --> 00:07:08,535
I really don't think she's here.

52
00:07:18,445 --> 00:07:19,445
Watch your step.

53
00:07:20,955 --> 00:07:21,955
Thanks.

54
00:07:23,815 --> 00:07:24,825
Should we get going?

55
00:07:29,295 --> 00:07:32,025
Let me try calling one
more time, just in case.

56
00:07:45,645 --> 00:07:46,775
(Lee Seon Hwa)

57
00:08:36,325 --> 00:08:37,625
Min Seo, are you all right?

58
00:08:43,435 --> 00:08:46,035
Hang on a second. I'm calling it in first.

59
00:09:23,175 --> 00:09:24,575
(Investigation in progress)

60
00:09:32,085 --> 00:09:33,215
How did you know her?

61
00:09:34,015 --> 00:09:35,415
She was a witness in our case.

62
00:09:35,885 --> 00:09:37,701
We haven't been able to
reach her since yesterday.

63
00:09:37,725 --> 00:09:40,285
What's the cause of death?
An overdose, you think?

64
00:09:42,895 --> 00:09:44,575
That's what it looks like at first glance.

65
00:09:47,595 --> 00:09:50,295
- Do you see this?
- Are those ligature marks?

66
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:51,965
Min Seo.

67
00:09:54,105 --> 00:09:58,645
We'll have to see if this was
an accident or a homicide.

68
00:10:00,775 --> 00:10:02,345
A laptop is missing.

69
00:10:04,385 --> 00:10:07,115
- A laptop?
- It had critical information on it,

70
00:10:07,685 --> 00:10:09,715
but it went missing
from our office yesterday.

71
00:10:10,455 --> 00:10:12,185
Right after Lee Seon Hwa visited. But

72
00:10:13,285 --> 00:10:14,725
I don't see it anywhere around here.

73
00:10:16,095 --> 00:10:17,215
What kind of data was on it?

74
00:10:18,795 --> 00:10:20,225
That's complicated.

75
00:10:20,495 --> 00:10:22,565
How did you know she'd be here?

76
00:10:25,535 --> 00:10:27,305
She and Min Seo knew each other.

77
00:10:29,075 --> 00:10:30,075
So

78
00:10:30,575 --> 00:10:32,375
You're the one who
told her about this place?

79
00:10:35,015 --> 00:10:37,645
- Excuse me, Detective Kim.
- Seung Jin.

80
00:10:37,915 --> 00:10:39,345
This isn't indoors.

81
00:10:40,415 --> 00:10:41,415
Detective Gu!

82
00:10:43,785 --> 00:10:46,285
There's no CCTV around
here. It's too secluded.

83
00:10:46,555 --> 00:10:48,555
But there's a car parked
on the road up ahead,

84
00:10:48,625 --> 00:10:50,001
and I've secured its dashcam footage.

85
00:10:50,025 --> 00:10:51,095
- Let me see.
- Yes, sir.

86
00:10:51,165 --> 00:10:52,325
Do you mind if I take a look?

87
00:10:53,765 --> 00:10:54,765
Excuse me.

88
00:10:56,765 --> 00:10:58,265
Could I bum a cigarette?

89
00:11:01,575 --> 00:11:02,575
Are you nuts?

90
00:11:04,505 --> 00:11:06,975
What? It's not like we're strangers.

91
00:11:09,815 --> 00:11:12,515
- What is it?
- What? Nothing.

92
00:11:22,055 --> 00:11:23,055
That's him, right?

93
00:11:23,795 --> 00:11:25,355
The same culprit from Hyeon Jin's case.

94
00:11:29,935 --> 00:11:32,965
Detective Gu brought this
photo. Find out who it is.

95
00:11:52,685 --> 00:11:54,925
- First, canvass the neighbourhood.
- Yes, sir.

96
00:11:55,725 --> 00:11:58,225
Ra Young. Hold on a second.

97
00:12:03,935 --> 00:12:06,565
Are you out of your mind? You
got a death wish or something?

98
00:12:10,135 --> 00:12:12,845
I'm pissed enough as it is
with this being messed up.

99
00:12:13,875 --> 00:12:14,875
Give me the cigarette.

100
00:12:19,845 --> 00:12:20,845
I dropped it.

101
00:12:21,385 --> 00:12:22,385
What?

102
00:12:38,765 --> 00:12:41,175
Who did this? Was it
Prosecutor Park Je Yeol?

103
00:12:41,935 --> 00:12:44,745
Why would he go this far?
And what was on that laptop?

104
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:47,495
If you need me for more
questioning, you can call me.

105
00:12:50,415 --> 00:12:52,591
Why are you going to
such lengths to hide this?

106
00:12:52,615 --> 00:12:54,121
What if this puts Hyeon
Jin in danger again?

107
00:12:54,145 --> 00:12:56,425
They have an accomplice.
Someone inside the police force.

108
00:12:58,455 --> 00:12:59,455
What did you just say?

109
00:13:00,925 --> 00:13:02,955
I'm sorry. I'm just on edge.

110
00:13:06,865 --> 00:13:09,165
I understand. We'll talk later.

111
00:13:10,465 --> 00:13:12,041
It's a shame we met like this.

112
00:13:12,065 --> 00:13:14,065
I didn't even get to
congratulate you on the baby.

113
00:13:15,505 --> 00:13:16,705
I guess you haven't heard yet.

114
00:13:17,675 --> 00:13:18,675
Sorry?

115
00:13:20,175 --> 00:13:21,175
You should head in, then.

116
00:13:28,585 --> 00:13:29,585
That brat

117
00:13:30,255 --> 00:13:31,695
I'll kill her with my own two hands.

118
00:13:34,925 --> 00:13:35,925
Seung Jin!

119
00:13:37,325 --> 00:13:39,325
Gosh, where did he run off to?

120
00:13:48,805 --> 00:13:50,205
Seung Jin! What are you doing?

121
00:13:50,505 --> 00:13:51,505
Hey.

122
00:13:53,005 --> 00:13:54,715
The cigarette butt.

123
00:13:55,275 --> 00:13:57,395
You're the one who told
me to take care of it, right?

124
00:13:58,615 --> 00:13:59,615
Is the lawyer gone?

125
00:14:02,655 --> 00:14:03,655
All right.

126
00:14:05,085 --> 00:14:06,085
Let's go.

127
00:14:11,425 --> 00:14:12,785
You're not feeling great, are you?

128
00:14:17,865 --> 00:14:19,705
If I still can't bring myself to forgive them,

129
00:14:20,065 --> 00:14:21,705
does that mean something's wrong with me?

130
00:14:24,135 --> 00:14:26,605
Sometimes, forgiveness
isn't the right answer.

131
00:14:29,845 --> 00:14:30,845
Then

132
00:14:31,985 --> 00:14:33,985
what am I supposed to
do in a situation like this?

133
00:14:36,085 --> 00:14:37,085
You just

134
00:14:38,125 --> 00:14:40,425
have to take it one day at a time.

135
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:44,795
Some days, you'll hate them,
and other days, you'll be in agony.

136
00:14:47,395 --> 00:14:49,165
Then one day, you'll suddenly look back,

137
00:14:49,635 --> 00:14:52,765
and see just how far you've come,
carrying that memory with you.

138
00:14:53,565 --> 00:14:54,575
And when you do,

139
00:14:55,305 --> 00:14:56,435
it'll feel a little better.

140
00:14:57,745 --> 00:14:59,405
Even if the wound never fully heals,

141
00:14:59,705 --> 00:15:01,225
you'll find that even with your scars,

142
00:15:01,375 --> 00:15:05,285
you can still keep moving forward.

143
00:15:08,615 --> 00:15:10,861
It's okay if you can't forgive.
And it's okay if you can't forget.

144
00:15:10,885 --> 00:15:13,655
Just try to get through each day.

145
00:15:14,595 --> 00:15:15,795
Just like I did.

146
00:15:34,045 --> 00:15:36,475
I'm mean and selfish.

147
00:15:36,875 --> 00:15:38,715
I've been a total mess lately.

148
00:15:39,715 --> 00:15:41,615
But still, she didn't deserve this.

149
00:15:43,685 --> 00:15:45,885
They're going to pay the price.

150
00:15:46,385 --> 00:15:48,455
Every last person involved with Connect.

151
00:15:50,025 --> 00:15:51,265
I assume they're the ones

152
00:15:51,595 --> 00:15:53,025
who took the laptop?

153
00:16:00,765 --> 00:16:01,775
It's okay to tell him.

154
00:16:02,975 --> 00:16:05,145
- What?
- What happened with Park Je Yeol.

155
00:16:05,845 --> 00:16:09,215
If you've been holding back from
telling Seon Kyu because of me,

156
00:16:09,615 --> 00:16:10,975
it's okay to tell him now.

157
00:16:11,445 --> 00:16:12,445
I'm against it.

158
00:16:12,885 --> 00:16:15,215
At least, not until this
case is completely over.

159
00:16:15,655 --> 00:16:17,515
That's for Hyeon Jin to decide now.

160
00:16:18,185 --> 00:16:21,995
If Connect infiltrated the police,
we might need Seon Kyu's help.

161
00:16:25,325 --> 00:16:26,465
I might

162
00:16:27,265 --> 00:16:29,395
end up divorcing him.

163
00:16:30,135 --> 00:16:31,135
What?

164
00:16:32,165 --> 00:16:34,235
The baby might not be his.

165
00:16:34,705 --> 00:16:36,875
What on earth are you
talking about? Then whose...

166
00:16:39,005 --> 00:16:40,005
Don't tell me...

167
00:16:40,505 --> 00:16:41,545
Is it Reporter Lee's?

168
00:16:44,585 --> 00:16:47,815
- They said it's a possibility.
- Hwang Hyeon Jin!

169
00:16:49,815 --> 00:16:51,725
I regret it so much, it's driving me crazy.

170
00:16:52,485 --> 00:16:54,725
I feel so bad for Seon
Kyu, I could just die.

171
00:16:55,025 --> 00:16:57,965
If I could turn back time, I would!

172
00:16:58,465 --> 00:17:01,395
But what am I supposed
to do? It already happened,

173
00:17:01,895 --> 00:17:03,265
and I'm the one who did it.

174
00:17:13,875 --> 00:17:15,975
Get up. Let's go get something to eat.

175
00:17:21,515 --> 00:17:23,955
Use this. Get something nice and expensive.

176
00:17:24,415 --> 00:17:25,455
You're not coming with us?

177
00:17:25,985 --> 00:17:26,985
I have plans.

178
00:17:27,685 --> 00:17:31,925
It's one thing to make mistakes,
hurt people, and do wrong,

179
00:17:32,425 --> 00:17:33,985
but you have to clean up your own mess.

180
00:17:34,565 --> 00:17:38,265
If you act like a coward at our
age, there's no coming back from it.

181
00:17:38,905 --> 00:17:40,735
Where are you going? What plans?

182
00:17:42,505 --> 00:17:44,135
I'm going to marry CEO Baek.

183
00:17:45,505 --> 00:17:46,505
Are you serious?

184
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:51,121
Why do you always announce
your marriage like that?

185
00:17:51,145 --> 00:17:52,745
It's not like you're ordering food.

186
00:17:54,045 --> 00:17:55,055
I'm going to be late.

187
00:17:55,855 --> 00:17:58,925
Haeil won't push us around anymore.
Just hang in there a little longer.

188
00:18:24,815 --> 00:18:28,485
All that talk about justice, and
this is what you do in the end.

189
00:18:29,415 --> 00:18:31,555
- Where's CEO Baek?
- He's waiting inside.

190
00:18:36,995 --> 00:18:38,395
Why aren't you asking me this time?

191
00:18:38,825 --> 00:18:40,195
Why I chose CEO Baek.

192
00:18:40,965 --> 00:18:43,535
For your first marriage, and your second,

193
00:18:43,695 --> 00:18:46,035
you fought me on every single little thing.

194
00:18:47,105 --> 00:18:49,375
You must have figured
he'd be easy to control.

195
00:18:50,335 --> 00:18:52,295
He doesn't have a powerful
family backing him up.

196
00:18:53,475 --> 00:18:55,145
Men like that are a dime a dozen.

197
00:18:57,045 --> 00:18:58,045
Then why him?

198
00:18:59,515 --> 00:19:00,955
You two are cut from the same cloth.

199
00:19:02,255 --> 00:19:05,855
There may not be love, but
he'll be able to understand you.

200
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:09,395
That's the impression I got.

201
00:19:11,225 --> 00:19:12,225
As for Jung Hyeon.

202
00:19:17,835 --> 00:19:19,715
If you're really that
uncomfortable seeing him,

203
00:19:20,205 --> 00:19:21,905
I'll have him reassigned.

204
00:19:23,235 --> 00:19:24,235
After the wedding.

205
00:19:24,905 --> 00:19:25,905
That won't be necessary.

206
00:19:27,345 --> 00:19:28,815
You don't need to do that anymore.

207
00:19:42,295 --> 00:19:43,615
The press release is already out,

208
00:19:43,995 --> 00:19:46,155
so we're thinking of skipping
the engagement ceremony.

209
00:19:46,765 --> 00:19:49,965
That must have been her idea.
She always finds them a hassle.

210
00:19:50,665 --> 00:19:53,435
Well, moving up the
wedding isn't a bad idea either.

211
00:19:54,005 --> 00:19:55,975
The two of you can decide on a date.

212
00:19:56,305 --> 00:19:59,075
Picking an auspicious date,
following all the traditions

213
00:19:59,475 --> 00:20:01,035
I can't stand all that nonsense either.

214
00:20:01,145 --> 00:20:02,645
I'll discuss it with Shin Jae.

215
00:20:04,985 --> 00:20:08,755
I didn't take you for the type,
but it's always "Shin Jae."

216
00:20:09,055 --> 00:20:11,091
So you're the doting-husband type,
CEO Baek? Is that what you are?

217
00:20:11,115 --> 00:20:13,225
I'll do everything in my power for her

218
00:20:13,285 --> 00:20:14,855
if it's what Shin Jae wants.

219
00:20:16,355 --> 00:20:17,995
My daughter is so lucky.

220
00:20:19,825 --> 00:20:21,795
LnJ is leaving Haeil.

221
00:20:23,065 --> 00:20:24,195
It's going independent

222
00:20:24,265 --> 00:20:25,635
along with my marriage.

223
00:20:28,375 --> 00:20:30,335
I'm supposed to get it as a wedding gift.

224
00:20:30,505 --> 00:20:31,505
A non-profit foundation.

225
00:20:37,545 --> 00:20:38,985
It's what Shin Jae wants.

226
00:20:41,715 --> 00:20:45,185
I'm sure you know what it
really means to start one.

227
00:20:45,925 --> 00:20:49,755
It means Shin Jae has no
intention of inheriting Haeil, right?

228
00:20:52,595 --> 00:20:56,235
- And you're okay with that?
- If Shin Jae is okay with it,

229
00:20:56,895 --> 00:20:58,165
then I'm okay with it too.

230
00:21:02,005 --> 00:21:03,005
I

231
00:21:03,835 --> 00:21:07,205
didn't raise my daughter
just to be some chaebol's wife.

232
00:21:07,605 --> 00:21:11,545
That's a big reason why
she's been divorced twice.

233
00:21:14,015 --> 00:21:17,915
It doesn't matter to me what
Shin Jae becomes or doesn't.

234
00:21:18,085 --> 00:21:20,725
She should be the one to
decide what she wants and do it.

235
00:21:21,025 --> 00:21:22,455
Whatever she decides,

236
00:21:22,755 --> 00:21:25,865
I'll be right by her side to support her.

237
00:21:34,905 --> 00:21:36,835
So you'll take the axe I gave you,

238
00:21:38,745 --> 00:21:40,475
and strike me with it?

239
00:21:43,675 --> 00:21:45,145
It's my life, isn't it?

240
00:21:46,615 --> 00:21:49,755
I'm the one in the driver's seat now, Mom.

241
00:22:01,595 --> 00:22:04,195
You really have no concept of money.

242
00:22:04,595 --> 00:22:06,435
Throwing up all that expensive food.

243
00:22:16,215 --> 00:22:17,215
Honey?

244
00:22:18,745 --> 00:22:21,045
You're home late.

245
00:22:22,955 --> 00:22:24,985
You should've told me you were coming.

246
00:22:27,885 --> 00:22:31,595
No, it's just... I get nauseous
on an empty stomach,

247
00:22:31,895 --> 00:22:33,995
but then I feel sick when
I actually eat something.

248
00:22:34,765 --> 00:22:37,335
You can do that later. Come sit down.

249
00:22:49,515 --> 00:22:50,545
What are you doing?

250
00:22:51,075 --> 00:22:52,085
Sit.

251
00:22:53,685 --> 00:22:56,185
I still have some shame.

252
00:22:56,555 --> 00:22:59,755
I'm not so shameless
that I can eat the food

253
00:23:00,025 --> 00:23:01,425
you made for me right now.

254
00:23:05,995 --> 00:23:07,825
And you have to be this clueless too?

255
00:23:08,395 --> 00:23:09,395
Eat.

256
00:23:10,195 --> 00:23:11,495
It's not the baby's fault.

257
00:23:57,215 --> 00:24:00,715
The green hoodie who attacked
you killed Lee Seon Hwa.

258
00:24:00,985 --> 00:24:04,285
You already know that, right?
I'm sure Ra Young already told you.

259
00:24:05,285 --> 00:24:06,285
Yes.

260
00:24:13,025 --> 00:24:14,095
I want to hear it.

261
00:24:14,625 --> 00:24:16,695
Everything that happened to you.

262
00:24:18,195 --> 00:24:20,065
If this is because you
still don't trust me...

263
00:24:20,135 --> 00:24:21,405
That's not it.

264
00:24:22,275 --> 00:24:24,675
It wasn't because I didn't trust you.

265
00:24:25,345 --> 00:24:27,905
It's because I didn't go through it alone.

266
00:24:30,315 --> 00:24:32,615
Even though we're husband and wife,

267
00:24:33,485 --> 00:24:36,285
speaking recklessly about a
pain that isn't mine to share

268
00:24:37,355 --> 00:24:39,685
I didn't believe it was my place to do so.

269
00:24:41,055 --> 00:24:42,055
And

270
00:24:44,395 --> 00:24:46,795
I didn't want to burden you.

271
00:24:47,225 --> 00:24:49,995
I knew you would have been torn.

272
00:24:50,935 --> 00:24:53,435
Between being a detective
and being my husband.

273
00:24:58,005 --> 00:25:00,045
This is going to be a long story.

274
00:25:01,475 --> 00:25:03,515
And there are parts that will be painful,

275
00:25:04,645 --> 00:25:05,815
for you to hear.

276
00:25:12,555 --> 00:25:13,755
I'm prepared for that.

277
00:25:21,765 --> 00:25:23,765
So, how does it feel to
declare your independence?

278
00:25:24,165 --> 00:25:25,265
Liberating?

279
00:25:27,565 --> 00:25:29,475
I doubt this is the end of it.

280
00:25:30,605 --> 00:25:31,975
My mother has never once

281
00:25:32,905 --> 00:25:34,375
backed down in her life.

282
00:25:36,675 --> 00:25:38,515
Do you know what's so scary about that?

283
00:25:39,715 --> 00:25:41,785
It means she doesn't know how to give up.

284
00:25:42,385 --> 00:25:45,585
And here I was thinking
that went well comparatively.

285
00:25:46,955 --> 00:25:49,825
The calm before the storm? Or
are we in the eye of the storm?

286
00:25:50,925 --> 00:25:52,595
Does that scare you?

287
00:25:55,735 --> 00:25:58,465
- How about one more drink?
- I'd like that.

288
00:25:58,705 --> 00:25:59,835
At my place.

289
00:26:05,505 --> 00:26:08,375
You know what the difference
is between my mother and me?

290
00:26:10,145 --> 00:26:12,285
I've been knocked down
more times than I can count.

291
00:26:12,845 --> 00:26:14,845
And I've come back
fighting every single time.

292
00:26:17,985 --> 00:26:19,625
I'm going to see this through to the end.

293
00:26:20,425 --> 00:26:22,225
Whatever storm comes,

294
00:26:23,125 --> 00:26:24,625
I'll fight my way through it.

295
00:26:58,895 --> 00:27:03,065
A woman in her 20s was found dead
in an abandoned building in Seoul.

296
00:27:03,335 --> 00:27:06,665
A blood test revealed
a lethal dose of a drug,

297
00:27:06,905 --> 00:27:10,575
and police have requested an autopsy
after finding evidence of foul play.

298
00:27:21,385 --> 00:27:22,385
Sang A.

299
00:27:22,655 --> 00:27:25,325
Dad, I'm late. Hurry up.

300
00:27:29,155 --> 00:27:31,225
- What's with Sang A?
- I don't know.

301
00:27:32,125 --> 00:27:33,865
Maybe you should ask yourself that.

302
00:27:43,305 --> 00:27:45,675
What's wrong, sweetie?
Did something happen?

303
00:27:55,885 --> 00:27:56,885
Mom

304
00:27:57,615 --> 00:27:59,525
I thought her treatment was over.

305
00:28:02,025 --> 00:28:04,725
Your mom let you down again, didn't she?

306
00:28:06,395 --> 00:28:08,735
You and I always try so hard,

307
00:28:09,595 --> 00:28:12,105
so why does your mom
always have to make us so sad?

308
00:28:23,645 --> 00:28:25,245
(Mujin National Forensic Service)

309
00:28:28,285 --> 00:28:29,315
Ms. Hong Yeon Hee.

310
00:28:31,755 --> 00:28:32,955
I need a word with you.

311
00:28:33,225 --> 00:28:35,255
- I'm running late.
- It'll only take a minute.

312
00:28:39,295 --> 00:28:40,665
Why haven't you called?

313
00:28:43,435 --> 00:28:45,965
I understand you're nervous,
and I know why you're hesitating.

314
00:28:46,035 --> 00:28:47,835
- But...
- Let me make one thing clear.

315
00:28:48,805 --> 00:28:50,835
I want nothing to do with any of this.

316
00:28:51,105 --> 00:28:52,875
- Ms. Hong.
- I hope we don't meet again.

317
00:28:52,945 --> 00:28:56,245
Yesterday, a body was brought in, right?

318
00:28:56,515 --> 00:28:58,515
Cause of death, drug
overdose. A woman in her 20s.

319
00:29:00,785 --> 00:29:02,115
Park Je Yeol killed her.

320
00:29:03,455 --> 00:29:05,431
- What are you talking about?
- The reason I asked you

321
00:29:05,455 --> 00:29:06,625
to cloning his phone

322
00:29:07,625 --> 00:29:08,995
was because of an app.

323
00:29:09,755 --> 00:29:10,895
A prostitution app.

324
00:29:21,465 --> 00:29:24,475
(Prosecutor's Office)

325
00:29:51,195 --> 00:29:53,835
I'm disappointed our agreement
wasn't properly honoured.

326
00:29:55,775 --> 00:29:58,105
There's no cause for concern.

327
00:30:00,145 --> 00:30:02,845
That's what you said
when that reporter died.

328
00:30:03,875 --> 00:30:07,445
And yet, where is that
reporter's laptop now?

329
00:30:10,185 --> 00:30:13,925
You still haven't identified
who took the laptop.

330
00:30:15,185 --> 00:30:16,555
We're still looking for it.

331
00:30:18,225 --> 00:30:21,925
You promised us the highest
level of security and safety.

332
00:30:22,565 --> 00:30:27,435
You'd do well to remember
how someone like you

333
00:30:28,675 --> 00:30:30,205
got to where you are today.

334
00:31:18,955 --> 00:31:20,725
(Lee Da Eun)

335
00:31:20,785 --> 00:31:21,955
I looked into her.

336
00:31:22,055 --> 00:31:25,025
Park Je Yeol gave her a
suspension of indictment a while back.

337
00:31:25,095 --> 00:31:29,165
Suspended for aggravated
assault. Smells fishy, doesn't it?

338
00:31:29,935 --> 00:31:32,105
Her only family is a
younger sibling, a minor.

339
00:31:32,665 --> 00:31:35,265
Like you said, it seems he
targets vulnerable young people.

340
00:31:35,675 --> 00:31:37,355
There's also what happened with Yoo Jeong.

341
00:31:37,535 --> 00:31:40,705
Lee Seon Hwa was murdered
even though she gave us intel.

342
00:31:41,045 --> 00:31:43,115
The other victims could be in danger too.

343
00:31:43,915 --> 00:31:46,285
Got it. I'll start by finding Lee Da Eun.

344
00:31:46,345 --> 00:31:47,845
(Lee Da Eun)

345
00:31:56,395 --> 00:31:57,855
- Hey, rookie.
- Yes?

346
00:31:57,925 --> 00:31:58,925
Where'd Detective Kim go?

347
00:31:58,995 --> 00:32:01,825
Detective Kim? He said he was
just stepping out for a moment.

348
00:32:03,595 --> 00:32:06,005
- All right. I'm heading out.
- Yes, sir.

349
00:32:06,065 --> 00:32:09,635
(Seoul Mujin Police Station)

350
00:32:38,495 --> 00:32:40,141
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

351
00:32:40,165 --> 00:32:41,835
On the syringe from the scene,

352
00:32:41,905 --> 00:32:44,345
- we found a fingerprint.
- What about inside the department?

353
00:32:45,035 --> 00:32:48,605
No one at the station
knows yet. I acted on my own.

354
00:33:04,125 --> 00:33:05,295
Was this all you?

355
00:33:14,565 --> 00:33:17,235
I thought I could use
you as a double agent,

356
00:33:17,805 --> 00:33:20,245
but you wouldn't follow a
single one of our orders.

357
00:33:21,005 --> 00:33:24,575
I figured you'd completely
thrown in your lot with LnJ.

358
00:33:24,645 --> 00:33:25,915
But that wasn't it either.

359
00:33:27,585 --> 00:33:30,685
You were hiding your own agenda all along.

360
00:33:42,735 --> 00:33:44,095
Who are you, really?

361
00:33:49,005 --> 00:33:50,235
Where's the laptop?

362
00:33:50,675 --> 00:33:51,675
I don't know.

363
00:33:52,345 --> 00:33:53,345
Really?

364
00:33:54,405 --> 00:33:55,715
Then I'll help you remember.

365
00:34:01,145 --> 00:34:03,485
You're going to regret everything.

366
00:34:05,925 --> 00:34:07,255
Even the day you were born.

367
00:34:20,305 --> 00:34:22,375
- Shall we begin?
- Yes.

368
00:34:30,645 --> 00:34:32,045
Park Je Yeol killed her.

369
00:34:44,295 --> 00:34:46,325
Ma'am, are you all right?

370
00:34:47,265 --> 00:34:49,135
Yes, I'm fine.

371
00:34:57,975 --> 00:35:01,775
Now you see, don't you?
Why that USB is so necessary.

372
00:35:04,715 --> 00:35:05,815
But

373
00:35:06,145 --> 00:35:09,785
I meant it when I said I
wanted to get you out.

374
00:35:10,285 --> 00:35:11,485
Why would you?

375
00:35:12,625 --> 00:35:13,625
Because maybe

376
00:35:15,025 --> 00:35:16,325
if I'd been less fortunate,

377
00:35:18,325 --> 00:35:20,465
I could have been in your shoes.

378
00:35:22,125 --> 00:35:25,235
Living under the same roof
as someone who might kill me,

379
00:35:27,005 --> 00:35:28,685
and desperately trying to save my child

380
00:35:28,935 --> 00:35:31,435
from that same fate.

381
00:36:19,025 --> 00:36:21,105
(The late Lee Seong Hyeok,
the late Park Jeong Yeon)

382
00:36:31,935 --> 00:36:34,465
(The late Lee Ga On)

383
00:36:57,755 --> 00:36:59,971
(The late Lee Seong Hyeok,
the late Park Jeong Yeon)

384
00:36:59,995 --> 00:37:02,225
(The late Lee Ga On)

385
00:37:04,935 --> 00:37:08,235
(The late Lee Ga On)

386
00:37:17,475 --> 00:37:19,715
I didn't mention it on purpose,
but you all came anyway.

387
00:37:20,515 --> 00:37:21,515
Hey.

388
00:37:22,715 --> 00:37:24,515
Did you really think we'd forget this day?

389
00:37:25,755 --> 00:37:27,755
What do you think?
For this year's birthday,

390
00:37:27,825 --> 00:37:29,595
I picked something a little more colourful.

391
00:37:35,265 --> 00:37:36,411
(The late Lee Seong Hyeok,
the late Park Jeong Yeon)

392
00:37:36,435 --> 00:37:37,565
(The late Lee Ga On)

393
00:37:56,055 --> 00:37:57,375
Would things have been different?

394
00:38:00,955 --> 00:38:03,725
If that incident hadn't
happened when I was in my 20s,

395
00:38:04,225 --> 00:38:05,865
but a little later in life...

396
00:38:07,025 --> 00:38:08,025
If I

397
00:38:08,595 --> 00:38:10,235
had been a stronger person.

398
00:38:12,605 --> 00:38:15,005
And if I hadn't put my
child up for adoption,

399
00:38:15,735 --> 00:38:17,635
and had made a different choice.

400
00:38:18,605 --> 00:38:19,605
I wonder if maybe...

401
00:38:21,175 --> 00:38:22,915
Would everything have been different?

402
00:38:23,745 --> 00:38:26,485
At no age are you strong
enough to handle that.

403
00:38:31,715 --> 00:38:33,455
You had the right to choose

404
00:38:34,125 --> 00:38:36,325
how you wanted to live your own life.

405
00:38:36,625 --> 00:38:38,825
No one has the right to judge your choice.

406
00:38:42,065 --> 00:38:43,871
(The late Park Jeong
Yeon, the late Lee Ga On)

407
00:38:43,895 --> 00:38:45,235
Do you really think so?

408
00:38:53,445 --> 00:38:54,775
You've never regretted it?

409
00:38:55,305 --> 00:38:56,345
That day,

410
00:38:57,945 --> 00:38:59,445
you guys coming to save me.

411
00:39:01,215 --> 00:39:04,755
If we hadn't gone, you could have died.

412
00:39:07,125 --> 00:39:10,595
Of course, it would've been
better if it never happened at all.

413
00:39:11,995 --> 00:39:15,835
Then Shin Jae would've taken
over her mom's company quietly,

414
00:39:16,665 --> 00:39:19,605
and I wouldn't have the
nightmare of waking up in prison,

415
00:39:19,805 --> 00:39:22,035
haunting me for the rest of my life.

416
00:39:22,635 --> 00:39:25,035
A lawyer for sexual assault survivors.

417
00:39:25,575 --> 00:39:28,645
My foot. I'd own three buildings by now.

418
00:39:28,805 --> 00:39:30,575
You know? Cleaning up after rich scumbags.

419
00:39:31,945 --> 00:39:34,945
She'd be on TV, you know?
Arguing against you on a panel.

420
00:39:37,155 --> 00:39:41,125
And as for you, you'd still be smiling now,

421
00:39:41,825 --> 00:39:44,895
like you were before it happened,
without a care in the world.

422
00:39:46,525 --> 00:39:48,225
But even if I could turn back time,

423
00:39:48,525 --> 00:39:52,035
I'd do the same thing and go save you.

424
00:39:52,835 --> 00:39:55,165
For you, of course.

425
00:39:55,905 --> 00:39:59,135
But that's not the only reason.

426
00:39:59,775 --> 00:40:02,405
And for all the people we've
been able to help since then.

427
00:40:02,675 --> 00:40:04,195
I'd do it all over again for them too.

428
00:40:05,345 --> 00:40:07,685
I would do the same.

429
00:40:13,925 --> 00:40:16,005
(The late Lee Seong Hyeok,
the late Park Jeong Yeon)

430
00:40:16,625 --> 00:40:18,595
When I wake up in the morning,

431
00:40:19,125 --> 00:40:20,965
I still find myself wondering.

432
00:40:22,295 --> 00:40:23,565
What if all of this

433
00:40:25,035 --> 00:40:27,605
is just a terrible dream?

434
00:40:31,905 --> 00:40:35,245
If it's a bad dream, let's
keep dreaming it together.

435
00:40:36,145 --> 00:40:37,745
We'll be right there with you.

436
00:40:38,875 --> 00:40:40,285
In this nightmare.

437
00:41:06,075 --> 00:41:07,075
Well?

438
00:41:07,805 --> 00:41:09,145
You still don't get it?

439
00:41:11,675 --> 00:41:12,715
I don't know.

440
00:41:14,715 --> 00:41:15,845
Don't worry.

441
00:41:16,685 --> 00:41:18,715
I'm just getting started.

442
00:41:32,965 --> 00:41:35,035
I was going to leave your face alone,

443
00:41:35,835 --> 00:41:37,205
but you've left me no choice.

444
00:41:38,105 --> 00:41:40,105
Maybe if I carve something into your skin,

445
00:41:40,645 --> 00:41:42,475
you'll finally learn a lesson.

446
00:41:43,375 --> 00:41:44,375
Right?

447
00:41:47,885 --> 00:41:48,885
How about it?

448
00:41:49,585 --> 00:41:50,685
Still nothing?

449
00:41:55,225 --> 00:41:56,595
I don't know about the laptop.

450
00:41:57,825 --> 00:42:00,795
But I do know your wife
teamed up with them

451
00:42:00,865 --> 00:42:02,735
to mess you up.

452
00:42:07,565 --> 00:42:11,075
Please. Whatever tricks they're up to...

453
00:42:11,705 --> 00:42:13,645
Do you really think it will matter?

454
00:42:14,075 --> 00:42:16,915
Yoon Ra Young told her to clone your phone.

455
00:42:18,175 --> 00:42:19,485
I overheard their call.

456
00:42:21,285 --> 00:42:24,685
For all you know, LnJ
might already have it.

457
00:42:25,655 --> 00:42:27,885
The proof that you're Connect.

458
00:42:56,485 --> 00:42:57,525
What should I do with her?

459
00:42:58,615 --> 00:42:59,855
Let her go for now.

460
00:43:01,255 --> 00:43:04,795
If she just disappears,
they'll start causing trouble.

461
00:43:51,835 --> 00:43:53,075
You guys heading to the office?

462
00:43:53,375 --> 00:43:57,515
- I have to finish my statement.
- Me too.

463
00:43:57,575 --> 00:43:59,215
Okay, I'll see you at our spot later.

464
00:43:59,515 --> 00:44:00,745
I'm heading straight there.

465
00:44:04,155 --> 00:44:05,355
Goodness.

466
00:44:10,355 --> 00:44:11,355
It's Ms. Hong Yeon Hee.

467
00:44:12,325 --> 00:44:13,725
(Hong Yeon Hee)

468
00:44:15,525 --> 00:44:19,095
- Hello?
- I'll accept your offer, Ms. Yoon.

469
00:44:19,835 --> 00:44:21,535
But in return, you have to help me.

470
00:44:22,435 --> 00:44:23,435
Understood.

471
00:44:24,405 --> 00:44:26,745
- What? What'd she say?
- I'll call you later.

472
00:44:32,375 --> 00:44:33,845
(Husband)

473
00:44:41,655 --> 00:44:43,925
I'm here. I'll be waiting.

474
00:44:58,975 --> 00:45:00,605
Mom, what are you doing?

475
00:45:01,205 --> 00:45:02,375
Just the essentials.

476
00:45:02,805 --> 00:45:04,475
Pack only the absolute essentials. Hurry.

477
00:45:05,115 --> 00:45:07,785
- What's going on?
- We're getting out of here.

478
00:45:08,245 --> 00:45:09,585
What are you talking about?

479
00:45:11,955 --> 00:45:14,825
From now on, it's just
going to be the two of us.

480
00:45:15,285 --> 00:45:16,645
If you want to go, go by yourself.

481
00:45:18,695 --> 00:45:19,695
Sang A.

482
00:45:23,135 --> 00:45:24,135
Sang A.

483
00:45:26,235 --> 00:45:28,035
I know this must be hard for you to accept.

484
00:45:28,465 --> 00:45:31,375
But, Sang A, I have my reasons for this.

485
00:45:32,135 --> 00:45:33,675
Even if you don't understand,

486
00:45:34,245 --> 00:45:36,375
- please, just trust me...
- Trust you?

487
00:45:36,775 --> 00:45:37,775
You?

488
00:45:47,925 --> 00:45:50,855
You said you'd quit. You promised.

489
00:45:52,155 --> 00:45:53,265
Sang A, this is

490
00:45:53,465 --> 00:45:57,735
I know exactly what's
been going on in this house.

491
00:46:15,885 --> 00:46:19,015
Every time it happens, I get
scared you're going to die.

492
00:46:19,415 --> 00:46:21,255
Do you have any idea how scared I've been?

493
00:46:21,685 --> 00:46:23,895
And do you have any
idea how hard I'm trying?

494
00:46:24,695 --> 00:46:25,825
Thinking that if I did well,

495
00:46:27,225 --> 00:46:28,765
if Dad was in a good mood,

496
00:46:29,565 --> 00:46:31,295
I thought he wouldn't treat you like that.

497
00:46:32,935 --> 00:46:34,535
But Mom, what is this?

498
00:46:35,305 --> 00:46:39,435
- Sang A.
- If you do this, what can I do?

499
00:46:46,345 --> 00:46:47,345
Sang A.

500
00:46:50,255 --> 00:46:52,715
Sang A.

501
00:47:10,105 --> 00:47:12,105
(Where are you? What are you up to?)

502
00:47:12,175 --> 00:47:14,745
(I ran away. Fought with my mom.)

503
00:47:14,805 --> 00:47:17,315
(Want to meet up?)

504
00:47:24,885 --> 00:47:29,825
(Yes)

505
00:48:05,695 --> 00:48:08,165
I'm sorry. My meeting ran a little late.

506
00:48:08,925 --> 00:48:10,235
What a charming hobby.

507
00:48:11,065 --> 00:48:13,665
- Did you make all this yourself?
- Yes.

508
00:48:13,735 --> 00:48:15,705
(CEO Baek Tae Joo)

509
00:48:15,765 --> 00:48:17,875
Making these helps calm my mind.

510
00:48:18,635 --> 00:48:19,675
How should I put it?

511
00:48:20,175 --> 00:48:23,075
You see, even this tiny world
has its own balance and order.

512
00:48:25,675 --> 00:48:27,315
Is this one not finished yet?

513
00:48:29,715 --> 00:48:31,195
This one ran into a bit of a problem.

514
00:48:31,585 --> 00:48:35,655
